191VKImageAnalyzer *WebViewImpl::ensureImageAnalyzer()
192{
193 if (!m_imageAnalyzer) {
194 m_imageAnalyzerQueue = WorkQueue::create("WebKit image analyzer queue");
195 m_imageAnalyzer = adoptNS([PAL::allocVKImageAnalyzerInstance() init]);
196 [m_imageAnalyzer setCallbackQueue:m_imageAnalyzerQueue->dispatchQueue()];
197 }
198 return m_imageAnalyzer.get();
199}
200
201static RetainPtr<VKImageAnalyzerRequest> createImageAnalysisRequest(CGImageRef image, const URL& imageURL, const URL& pageURL, VKAnalysisTypes types)
202{
203 auto request = adoptNS([PAL::allocVKImageAnalyzerRequestInstance() initWithCGImage:image orientation:VKImageOrientationUp requestType:types]);
204 [request setImageURL:imageURL];
205 [request setPageURL:pageURL];
206 return request;
207}
208
209void WebViewImpl::requestTextRecognition(const URL& imageURL, const ShareableBitmap::Handle& imageData, CompletionHandler<void(WebCore::TextRecognitionResult&&)>&& completion)
210{
211 if (!isLiveTextAvailableAndEnabled()) {
212 completion({ });
213 return;
214 }
215
216 auto imageBitmap = ShareableBitmap::create(imageData);
217 if (!imageBitmap) {
218 completion({ });
219 return;
220 }
221
222 auto cgImage = imageBitmap->makeCGImage();
223 auto request = createImageAnalysisRequest(cgImage.get(), imageURL, [NSURL _web_URLWithWTFString:m_page->currentURL()], VKAnalysisTypeText);
224 auto startTime = MonotonicTime::now();
225 [ensureImageAnalyzer() processRequest:request.get() progressHandler:nil completionHandler:makeBlockPtr([completion = WTFMove(completion), startTime] (VKImageAnalysis *analysis, NSError *) mutable {
226 callOnMainRunLoop([completion = WTFMove(completion), result = makeTextRecognitionResult(analysis), startTime] () mutable {
227 RELEASE_LOG(Images, "Image analysis completed in %.0f ms (found text? %d)", (MonotonicTime::now() - startTime).milliseconds(), !result.isEmpty());
228 completion(WTFMove(result));
229 });
230 }).get()];
231}
232
233void WebViewImpl::computeHasImageAnalysisResults(const URL& imageURL, ShareableBitmap& imageBitmap, ImageAnalysisType type, CompletionHandler<void(bool)>&& completion)
234{
235 if (!isLiveTextAvailableAndEnabled()) {
236 completion(false);
237 return;
238 }
239
240 auto cgImage = imageBitmap.makeCGImage();
241 auto analysisType = type == ImageAnalysisType::VisualSearch ? VKAnalysisTypeVisualSearch : VKAnalysisTypeText;
242 auto request = createImageAnalysisRequest(cgImage.get(), imageURL, [NSURL _web_URLWithWTFString:m_page->currentURL()], analysisType);
243 auto startTime = MonotonicTime::now();
244 [ensureImageAnalyzer() processRequest:request.get() progressHandler:nil completionHandler:makeBlockPtr([completion = WTFMove(completion), startTime, analysisType] (VKImageAnalysis *analysis, NSError *) mutable {
245 BOOL result = [analysis hasResultsForAnalysisTypes:analysisType];
246 CFRunLoopPerformBlock(CFRunLoopGetMain(), (__bridge CFStringRef)NSEventTrackingRunLoopMode, makeBlockPtr([completion = WTFMove(completion), result, analysisType, startTime] () mutable {
247 RELEASE_LOG(Images, "Image analysis completed in %.0f ms (found %s? %d)", (MonotonicTime::now() - startTime).milliseconds(), analysisType == VKAnalysisTypeVisualSearch ? "visual search results" : "text", result);
248 completion(result);
249 }).get());
250 CFRunLoopWakeUp(CFRunLoopGetMain());
251 }).get()];
252}

340static void* keyValueObservingContext = &keyValueObservingContext;
341
342- (void)startObserving:(NSWindow *)window
343{
344 if (!window)
345 return;
346
347 NSNotificationCenter *defaultNotificationCenter = [NSNotificationCenter defaultCenter];
348
349 // An NSView derived object such as WKView cannot observe these notifications, because NSView itself observes them.
350 [defaultNotificationCenter addObserver:self selector:@selector(_windowDidOrderOffScreen:) name:@"NSWindowDidOrderOffScreenNotification" object:window];
351 [defaultNotificationCenter addObserver:self selector:@selector(_windowDidOrderOnScreen:) name:@"_NSWindowDidBecomeVisible" object:window];
352
353 [defaultNotificationCenter addObserver:self selector:@selector(_windowDidBecomeKey:) name:NSWindowDidBecomeKeyNotification object:nil];
354 [defaultNotificationCenter addObserver:self selector:@selector(_windowDidResignKey:) name:NSWindowDidResignKeyNotification object:nil];
355 [defaultNotificationCenter addObserver:self selector:@selector(_windowDidMiniaturize:) name:NSWindowDidMiniaturizeNotification object:window];
356 [defaultNotificationCenter addObserver:self selector:@selector(_windowDidDeminiaturize:) name:NSWindowDidDeminiaturizeNotification object:window];
357 [defaultNotificationCenter addObserver:self selector:@selector(_windowDidMove:) name:NSWindowDidMoveNotification object:window];
358 [defaultNotificationCenter addObserver:self selector:@selector(_windowDidResize:) name:NSWindowDidResizeNotification object:window];
359 [defaultNotificationCenter addObserver:self selector:@selector(_windowDidChangeBackingProperties:) name:NSWindowDidChangeBackingPropertiesNotification object:window];
360 [defaultNotificationCenter addObserver:self selector:@selector(_windowDidChangeScreen:) name:NSWindowDidChangeScreenNotification object:window];
361 [defaultNotificationCenter addObserver:self selector:@selector(_windowDidChangeLayerHosting:) name:@"_NSWindowDidChangeContentsHostedInLayerSurfaceNotification" object:window];
362 [defaultNotificationCenter addObserver:self selector:@selector(_windowDidChangeOcclusionState:) name:NSWindowDidChangeOcclusionStateNotification object:window];
363
364 [defaultNotificationCenter addObserver:self selector:@selector(_screenDidChangeColorSpace:) name:NSScreenColorSpaceDidChangeNotification object:nil];
365
366 [window addObserver:self forKeyPath:@"contentLayoutRect" options:NSKeyValueObservingOptionInitial context:keyValueObservingContext];
367 [window addObserver:self forKeyPath:@"titlebarAppearsTransparent" options:NSKeyValueObservingOptionInitial context:keyValueObservingContext];
368}
369
370- (void)stopObserving:(NSWindow *)window
371{
372 if (!window)
373 return;
374
375 NSNotificationCenter *defaultNotificationCenter = [NSNotificationCenter defaultCenter];
376
377 [defaultNotificationCenter removeObserver:self name:@"NSWindowDidOrderOffScreenNotification" object:window];
378 [defaultNotificationCenter removeObserver:self name:@"_NSWindowDidBecomeVisible" object:window];
379
380 [defaultNotificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSWindowDidBecomeKeyNotification object:nil];
381 [defaultNotificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSWindowDidResignKeyNotification object:nil];
382 [defaultNotificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSWindowDidMiniaturizeNotification object:window];
383 [defaultNotificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSWindowDidDeminiaturizeNotification object:window];
384 [defaultNotificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSWindowDidMoveNotification object:window];
385 [defaultNotificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSWindowDidResizeNotification object:window];
386 [defaultNotificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSWindowDidChangeBackingPropertiesNotification object:window];
387 [defaultNotificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSWindowDidChangeScreenNotification object:window];
388 [defaultNotificationCenter removeObserver:self name:@"_NSWindowDidChangeContentsHostedInLayerSurfaceNotification" object:window];
389 [defaultNotificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSWindowDidChangeOcclusionStateNotification object:window];
390
391 [defaultNotificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSScreenColorSpaceDidChangeNotification object:nil];
392
393 if (_impl->isEditable())
394 [[NSFontPanel sharedFontPanel] removeObserver:self forKeyPath:@"visible" context:keyValueObservingContext];
395 [window removeObserver:self forKeyPath:@"contentLayoutRect" context:keyValueObservingContext];
396 [window removeObserver:self forKeyPath:@"titlebarAppearsTransparent" context:keyValueObservingContext];
397}
398

401 [[NSFontPanel sharedFontPanel] addObserver:self forKeyPath:@"visible" options:0 context:keyValueObservingContext];
402}

412 [[NSNotificationCenter defaultCenter] addObserver:self selector:@selector(_dictionaryLookupPopoverWillClose:) name:PAL::get_Lookup_LUNotificationPopoverWillClose() object:nil];
413#endif
414}

482- (void)observeValueForKeyPath:(NSString *)keyPath ofObject:(id)object change:(NSDictionary *)change context:(void *)context
483{
484 if (context != keyValueObservingContext) {
485 [super observeValueForKeyPath:keyPath ofObject:object change:change context:context];
486 return;
487 }
488
489 if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"visible"] && [NSFontPanel sharedFontPanelExists] && object == [NSFontPanel sharedFontPanel]) {
490 _impl->updateFontManagerIfNeeded();
491 return;
492 }
493 if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"contentLayoutRect"] || [keyPath isEqualToString:@"titlebarAppearsTransparent"])
494 _impl->updateContentInsetsIfAutomatic();
495}

542@interface WKResponderChainSink : NSResponder {
543 NSResponder *_lastResponderInChain;
544 bool _didReceiveUnhandledCommand;
545}
546
547- (id)initWithResponderChain:(NSResponder *)chain;
548- (void)detach;
549- (bool)didReceiveUnhandledCommand;
550@end
551
552@implementation WKResponderChainSink
553
554- (id)initWithResponderChain:(NSResponder *)chain
555{
556 self = [super init];
557 if (!self)
558 return nil;
559 _lastResponderInChain = chain;
560 while (NSResponder *next = [_lastResponderInChain nextResponder])
561 _lastResponderInChain = next;
562 [_lastResponderInChain setNextResponder:self];
563 return self;
564}
565
566- (void)detach
567{
568 // This assumes that the responder chain was either unmodified since
569 // -initWithResponderChain: was called, or was modified in such a way
570 // that _lastResponderInChain is still in the chain, and self was not
571 // moved earlier in the chain than _lastResponderInChain.
572 NSResponder *responderBeforeSelf = _lastResponderInChain;
573 NSResponder *next = [responderBeforeSelf nextResponder];
574 for (; next && next != self; next = [next nextResponder])
575 responderBeforeSelf = next;
576
577 // Nothing to be done if we are no longer in the responder chain.
578 if (next != self)
579 return;
580
581 [responderBeforeSelf setNextResponder:[self nextResponder]];
582 _lastResponderInChain = nil;
583}
584
585- (bool)didReceiveUnhandledCommand
586{
587 return _didReceiveUnhandledCommand;
588}
589
590- (void)noResponderFor:(SEL)selector
591{
592 _didReceiveUnhandledCommand = true;
593}
594
595- (void)doCommandBySelector:(SEL)selector
596{
597 _didReceiveUnhandledCommand = true;
598}
599
600- (BOOL)tryToPerform:(SEL)action with:(id)object
601{
602 _didReceiveUnhandledCommand = true;
603 return YES;
604}

640 _webViewImpl = webViewImpl;
641
642 NSSegmentedControl *insertListControl = [NSSegmentedControl segmentedControlWithLabels:@[ WebCore::insertListTypeNone(), WebCore::insertListTypeBulleted(), WebCore::insertListTypeNumbered() ] trackingMode:NSSegmentSwitchTrackingSelectOne target:self action:@selector(_selectList:)];
643 [insertListControl setWidth:listControlSegmentWidth forSegment:noListSegment];
644 [insertListControl setWidth:listControlSegmentWidth forSegment:unorderedListSegment];
645 [insertListControl setWidth:listControlSegmentWidth forSegment:orderedListSegment];
646 insertListControl.font = [NSFont systemFontOfSize:15];
647
648 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_BEGIN
649 id segmentElement = NSAccessibilityUnignoredDescendant(insertListControl);
650 NSArray *segments = [segmentElement accessibilityAttributeValue:NSAccessibilityChildrenAttribute];
651 ASSERT(segments.count == 3);
652 [segments[noListSegment] accessibilitySetOverrideValue:WebCore::insertListTypeNone() forAttribute:NSAccessibilityDescriptionAttribute];
653 [segments[unorderedListSegment] accessibilitySetOverrideValue:WebCore::insertListTypeBulletedAccessibilityTitle() forAttribute:NSAccessibilityDescriptionAttribute];
654 [segments[orderedListSegment] accessibilitySetOverrideValue:WebCore::insertListTypeNumberedAccessibilityTitle() forAttribute:NSAccessibilityDescriptionAttribute];
655 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_END
656
657 self.view = insertListControl;
658
659 return self;
660}
661
662- (void)didDestroyView
663{
664 _webViewImpl = nullptr;
665}
666
667- (void)_selectList:(id)sender
668{
669 if (!_webViewImpl)
670 return;
671
672 NSSegmentedControl *insertListControl = (NSSegmentedControl *)self.view;
673 switch (insertListControl.selectedSegment) {
674 case noListSegment:
675 // There is no "remove list" edit command, but InsertOrderedList and InsertUnorderedList both
676 // behave as toggles, so we can invoke the appropriate edit command depending on our _currentListType
677 // to remove an existing list. We don't have to do anything if _currentListType is NoList.
678 if (_currentListType == WebKit::OrderedList)
679 _webViewImpl->page().executeEditCommand(@"InsertOrderedList", @"");
680 else if (_currentListType == WebKit::UnorderedList)
681 _webViewImpl->page().executeEditCommand(@"InsertUnorderedList", @"");
682 break;
683 case unorderedListSegment:
684 _webViewImpl->page().executeEditCommand(@"InsertUnorderedList", @"");
685 break;
686 case orderedListSegment:
687 _webViewImpl->page().executeEditCommand(@"InsertOrderedList", @"");
688 break;
689 }
690
691 _webViewImpl->dismissTextTouchBarPopoverItemWithIdentifier(NSTouchBarItemIdentifierTextList);
692}
693
694- (void)setCurrentListType:(WebKit::ListType)listType
695{
696 NSSegmentedControl *insertListControl = (NSSegmentedControl *)self.view;
697 switch (listType) {
698 case WebKit::NoList:
699 [insertListControl setSelected:YES forSegment:noListSegment];
700 break;
701 case WebKit::OrderedList:
702 [insertListControl setSelected:YES forSegment:orderedListSegment];
703 break;
704 case WebKit::UnorderedList:
705 [insertListControl setSelected:YES forSegment:unorderedListSegment];
706 break;
707 }
708
709 _currentListType = listType;
710}

1044NSTouchBar *WebViewImpl::makeTouchBar()
1045{
1046 if (!m_canCreateTouchBars) {
1047 m_canCreateTouchBars = true;
1048 updateTouchBar();
1049 }
1050 return m_currentTouchBar.get();
1051}
1052
1053void WebViewImpl::updateTouchBar()
1054{
1055 if (!m_canCreateTouchBars)
1056 return;
1057
1058 NSTouchBar *touchBar = nil;
1059 bool userActionRequirementsHaveBeenMet = m_requiresUserActionForEditingControlsManager ? m_page->hasHadSelectionChangesFromUserInteraction() : true;
1060 if (m_page->editorState().isContentEditable && !m_page->isTouchBarUpdateSupressedForHiddenContentEditable()) {
1061 updateTextTouchBar();
1062 if (userActionRequirementsHaveBeenMet)
1063 touchBar = textTouchBar();
1064 }
1065#if ENABLE(WEB_PLAYBACK_CONTROLS_MANAGER)
1066 else if (m_page->hasActiveVideoForControlsManager()) {
1067 updateMediaTouchBar();
1068 // If useMediaPlaybackControlsView() is true, then we are relying on the API client to display a popover version
1069 // of the media timeline in their own function bar. If it is false, then we will display the media timeline in our
1070 // function bar.
1071 if (!useMediaPlaybackControlsView())
1072 touchBar = [m_mediaTouchBarProvider respondsToSelector:@selector(touchBar)] ? [(id)m_mediaTouchBarProvider.get() touchBar] : [(id)m_mediaTouchBarProvider.get() touchBar];
1073 } else if ([m_mediaTouchBarProvider playbackControlsController]) {
1074 if (m_clientWantsMediaPlaybackControlsView) {
1075 if ([m_view respondsToSelector:@selector(_web_didRemoveMediaControlsManager)] && m_view.getAutoreleased() == [m_view window].firstResponder)
1076 [m_view _web_didRemoveMediaControlsManager];
1077 }
1078 [m_mediaTouchBarProvider setPlaybackControlsController:nil];
1079 [m_mediaPlaybackControlsView setPlaybackControlsController:nil];
1080 }
1081#endif
1082
1083 if (touchBar == m_currentTouchBar)
1084 return;
1085
1086 // If m_editableElementIsFocused is true, then we may have a non-editable selection right now just because
1087 // the user is clicking or tabbing between editable fields.
1088 if (m_editableElementIsFocused && touchBar != textTouchBar())
1089 return;
1090
1091 m_currentTouchBar = touchBar;
1092 [m_view willChangeValueForKey:@"touchBar"];
1093 [m_view setTouchBar:m_currentTouchBar.get()];
1094 [m_view didChangeValueForKey:@"touchBar"];
1095}
1096
1097NSCandidateListTouchBarItem *WebViewImpl::candidateListTouchBarItem() const
1098{
1099 if (m_page->editorState().isInPasswordField)
1100 return m_passwordTextCandidateListTouchBarItem.get();
1101 return isRichlyEditableForTouchBar() ? m_richTextCandidateListTouchBarItem.get() : m_plainTextCandidateListTouchBarItem.get();
1102}

1104#if ENABLE(WEB_PLAYBACK_CONTROLS_MANAGER)
1105AVTouchBarScrubber *WebViewImpl::mediaPlaybackControlsView() const
1106{
1107 if (m_page->hasActiveVideoForControlsManager())
1108 return m_mediaPlaybackControlsView.get();
1109 return nil;
1110}
1111#endif

1113bool WebViewImpl::useMediaPlaybackControlsView() const
1114{
1115#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
1116 if (hasFullScreenWindowController())
1117 return ![m_fullScreenWindowController isFullScreen];
1118#endif
1119 return m_clientWantsMediaPlaybackControlsView;
1120}

1122void WebViewImpl::dismissTextTouchBarPopoverItemWithIdentifier(NSString *identifier)
1123{
1124 NSTouchBarItem *foundItem = nil;
1125 for (NSTouchBarItem *item in textTouchBar().items) {
1126 if ([item.identifier isEqualToString:identifier]) {
1127 foundItem = item;
1128 break;
1129 }
1130
1131 if ([item.identifier isEqualToString:NSTouchBarItemIdentifierTextFormat]) {
1132 for (NSTouchBarItem *childItem in ((NSGroupTouchBarItem *)item).groupTouchBar.items) {
1133 if ([childItem.identifier isEqualToString:identifier]) {
1134 foundItem = childItem;
1135 break;
1136 }
1137 }
1138 break;
1139 }
1140 }
1141
1142 if ([foundItem isKindOfClass:[NSPopoverTouchBarItem class]])
1143 [(NSPopoverTouchBarItem *)foundItem dismissPopover:nil];
1144}

1180void WebViewImpl::setUpTextTouchBar(NSTouchBar *touchBar)
1181{
1182 NSSet<NSTouchBarItem *> *templateItems = nil;
1183 NSArray<NSTouchBarItemIdentifier> *defaultItemIdentifiers = nil;
1184 NSArray<NSTouchBarItemIdentifier> *customizationAllowedItemIdentifiers = nil;
1185
1186 if (touchBar == m_passwordTextTouchBar.get()) {
1187 templateItems = [NSMutableSet setWithObject:m_passwordTextCandidateListTouchBarItem.get()];
1188 defaultItemIdentifiers = passwordTextTouchBarDefaultItemIdentifiers();
1189 } else if (touchBar == m_richTextTouchBar.get()) {
1190 templateItems = [NSMutableSet setWithObject:m_richTextCandidateListTouchBarItem.get()];
1191 defaultItemIdentifiers = richTextTouchBarDefaultItemIdentifiers();
1192 customizationAllowedItemIdentifiers = textTouchBarCustomizationAllowedIdentifiers();
1193 } else if (touchBar == m_plainTextTouchBar.get()) {
1194 templateItems = [NSMutableSet setWithObject:m_plainTextCandidateListTouchBarItem.get()];
1195 defaultItemIdentifiers = plainTextTouchBarDefaultItemIdentifiers();
1196 customizationAllowedItemIdentifiers = textTouchBarCustomizationAllowedIdentifiers();
1197 }
1198
1199 [touchBar setDelegate:m_textTouchBarItemController.get()];
1200 [touchBar setTemplateItems:templateItems];
1201 [touchBar setDefaultItemIdentifiers:defaultItemIdentifiers];
1202 [touchBar setCustomizationAllowedItemIdentifiers:customizationAllowedItemIdentifiers];
1203
1204 if (NSGroupTouchBarItem *textFormatItem = (NSGroupTouchBarItem *)[touchBar itemForIdentifier:NSTouchBarItemIdentifierTextFormat])
1205 textFormatItem.groupTouchBar.customizationIdentifier = @"WKTextFormatTouchBar";
1206}

1220static NSTextAlignment nsTextAlignmentFromTextAlignment(TextAlignment textAlignment)
1221{
1222 NSTextAlignment nsTextAlignment;
1223 switch (textAlignment) {
1224 case NoAlignment:
1225 nsTextAlignment = NSTextAlignmentNatural;
1226 break;
1227 case LeftAlignment:
1228 nsTextAlignment = NSTextAlignmentLeft;
1229 break;
1230 case RightAlignment:
1231 nsTextAlignment = NSTextAlignmentRight;
1232 break;
1233 case CenterAlignment:
1234 nsTextAlignment = NSTextAlignmentCenter;
1235 break;
1236 case JustifiedAlignment:
1237 nsTextAlignment = NSTextAlignmentJustified;
1238 break;
1239 default:
1240 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1241 }
1242
1243 return nsTextAlignment;
1244}
1245
1246void WebViewImpl::updateTextTouchBar()
1247{
1248 if (!m_page->editorState().isContentEditable)
1249 return;
1250
1251 if (m_isUpdatingTextTouchBar)
1252 return;
1253
1254 SetForScope<bool> isUpdatingTextFunctionBar(m_isUpdatingTextTouchBar, true);
1255
1256 if (!m_textTouchBarItemController)
1257 m_textTouchBarItemController = adoptNS([[WKTextTouchBarItemController alloc] initWithWebViewImpl:this]);
1258
1259 if (!m_startedListeningToCustomizationEvents) {
1260 [[NSNotificationCenter defaultCenter] addObserver:m_textTouchBarItemController.get() selector:@selector(touchBarDidExitCustomization:) name:NSTouchBarDidExitCustomization object:nil];
1261 [[NSNotificationCenter defaultCenter] addObserver:m_textTouchBarItemController.get() selector:@selector(touchBarWillEnterCustomization:) name:NSTouchBarWillEnterCustomization object:nil];
1262 [[NSNotificationCenter defaultCenter] addObserver:m_textTouchBarItemController.get() selector:@selector(didChangeAutomaticTextCompletion:) name:NSSpellCheckerDidChangeAutomaticTextCompletionNotification object:nil];
1263
1264 m_startedListeningToCustomizationEvents = true;
1265 }
1266
1267 if (!m_richTextCandidateListTouchBarItem || !m_plainTextCandidateListTouchBarItem || !m_passwordTextCandidateListTouchBarItem) {
1268 m_richTextCandidateListTouchBarItem = adoptNS([[NSCandidateListTouchBarItem alloc] initWithIdentifier:NSTouchBarItemIdentifierCandidateList]);
1269 [m_richTextCandidateListTouchBarItem setDelegate:m_textTouchBarItemController.get()];
1270 m_plainTextCandidateListTouchBarItem = adoptNS([[NSCandidateListTouchBarItem alloc] initWithIdentifier:NSTouchBarItemIdentifierCandidateList]);
1271 [m_plainTextCandidateListTouchBarItem setDelegate:m_textTouchBarItemController.get()];
1272 m_passwordTextCandidateListTouchBarItem = adoptNS([[NSCandidateListTouchBarItem alloc] initWithIdentifier:NSTouchBarItemIdentifierCandidateList]);
1273 [m_passwordTextCandidateListTouchBarItem setDelegate:m_textTouchBarItemController.get()];
1274 requestCandidatesForSelectionIfNeeded();
1275 }
1276
1277 if (!m_richTextTouchBar) {
1278 m_richTextTouchBar = adoptNS([[NSTouchBar alloc] init]);
1279 setUpTextTouchBar(m_richTextTouchBar.get());
1280 [m_richTextTouchBar setCustomizationIdentifier:@"WKRichTextTouchBar"];
1281 }
1282
1283 if (!m_plainTextTouchBar) {
1284 m_plainTextTouchBar = adoptNS([[NSTouchBar alloc] init]);
1285 setUpTextTouchBar(m_plainTextTouchBar.get());
1286 [m_plainTextTouchBar setCustomizationIdentifier:@"WKPlainTextTouchBar"];
1287 }
1288
1289 if ([NSSpellChecker isAutomaticTextCompletionEnabled] && !m_isCustomizingTouchBar) {
1290 BOOL showCandidatesList = !m_page->editorState().selectionIsRange || m_isHandlingAcceptedCandidate;
1291 [candidateListTouchBarItem() updateWithInsertionPointVisibility:showCandidatesList];
1292 [m_view _didUpdateCandidateListVisibility:showCandidatesList];
1293 }
1294
1295 if (m_page->editorState().isInPasswordField) {
1296 if (!m_passwordTextTouchBar) {
1297 m_passwordTextTouchBar = adoptNS([[NSTouchBar alloc] init]);
1298 setUpTextTouchBar(m_passwordTextTouchBar.get());
1299 }
1300 [m_passwordTextCandidateListTouchBarItem setCandidates:@[ ] forSelectedRange:NSMakeRange(0, 0) inString:nil];
1301 }
1302
1303 NSTouchBar *textTouchBar = this->textTouchBar();

1308 // the text when changing selection throughout the document.

1315 [m_textTouchBarItemController setTextColor:nsColor(editorState.postLayoutData().textColor)];
1316 [[m_textTouchBarItemController textListTouchBarViewController] setCurrentListType:(ListType)m_page->editorState().postLayoutData().enclosingListType];
1317 [m_textTouchBarItemController setCurrentTextAlignment:nsTextAlignmentFromTextAlignment((TextAlignment)editorState.postLayoutData().textAlignment)];
1318 }
1319 BOOL isShowingCandidateListItem = [textTouchBar.defaultItemIdentifiers containsObject:NSTouchBarItemIdentifierCandidateList] && [NSSpellChecker isAutomaticTextReplacementEnabled];

1460static NSTrackingAreaOptions trackingAreaOptions()
1461{
1462 // Legacy style scrollbars have design details that rely on tracking the mouse all the time.
1463 NSTrackingAreaOptions options = NSTrackingMouseMoved | NSTrackingMouseEnteredAndExited | NSTrackingInVisibleRect | NSTrackingCursorUpdate;
1464 if (_NSRecommendedScrollerStyle() == NSScrollerStyleLegacy)
1465 options |= NSTrackingActiveAlways;
1466 else
1467 options |= NSTrackingActiveInKeyWindow;
1468 return options;
1469}

1471WebViewImpl::WebViewImpl(NSView <WebViewImplDelegate> *view, WKWebView *outerWebView, WebProcessPool& processPool, Ref<API::PageConfiguration>&& configuration)
1472 : m_view(view)
1473 , m_pageClient(makeUnique<PageClientImpl>(view, outerWebView))
1474 , m_page(processPool.createWebPage(*m_pageClient, WTFMove(configuration)))
1475 , m_needsViewFrameInWindowCoordinates(m_page->preferences().pluginsEnabled())
1476 , m_intrinsicContentSize(CGSizeMake(NSViewNoIntrinsicMetric, NSViewNoIntrinsicMetric))
1477 , m_layoutStrategy([WKViewLayoutStrategy layoutStrategyWithPage:m_page.get() view:view viewImpl:*this mode:kWKLayoutModeViewSize])
1478 , m_undoTarget(adoptNS([[WKEditorUndoTarget alloc] init]))
1479 , m_windowVisibilityObserver(adoptNS([[WKWindowVisibilityObserver alloc] initWithView:view impl:*this]))
1480 , m_accessibilitySettingsObserver(adoptNS([[WKAccessibilitySettingsObserver alloc] initWithImpl:*this]))
1481 , m_primaryTrackingArea(adoptNS([[NSTrackingArea alloc] initWithRect:view.frame options:trackingAreaOptions() owner:view userInfo:nil]))
1482{
1483 static_cast<PageClientImpl&>(*m_pageClient).setImpl(*this);
1484
1485 ASSERT(hasProcessPrivilege(ProcessPrivilege::CanCommunicateWithWindowServer));
1486 [NSApp registerServicesMenuSendTypes:PasteboardTypes::forSelection() returnTypes:PasteboardTypes::forEditing()];
1487
1488 [view addTrackingArea:m_primaryTrackingArea.get()];
1489
1490 for (NSView *subview in view.subviews) {
1491 if ([subview isKindOfClass:WKFlippedView.class]) {
1492 // A layer hosting view may have already been created and added to the view hierarchy
1493 // in the process of initializing the WKWebView from an NSCoder.
1494 m_layerHostingView = (WKFlippedView *)subview;
1495 [m_layerHostingView setFrame:[m_view bounds]];
1496 break;
1497 }
1498 }
1499
1500 if (!m_layerHostingView) {
1501 // Create an NSView that will host our layer tree.
1502 m_layerHostingView = adoptNS([[WKFlippedView alloc] initWithFrame:[m_view bounds]]);
1503 [view addSubview:m_layerHostingView.get() positioned:NSWindowBelow relativeTo:nil];
1504 }
1505
1506 // Create a root layer that will back the NSView.
1507 RetainPtr<CALayer> layer = adoptNS([[CALayer alloc] init]);
1508 [layer setDelegate:[WebActionDisablingCALayerDelegate shared]];
1509#ifndef NDEBUG
1510 [layer setName:@"Hosting root layer"];
1511#endif
1512
1513 [m_layerHostingView setLayer:layer.get()];
1514 [m_layerHostingView setWantsLayer:YES];
1515
1516 m_page->setIntrinsicDeviceScaleFactor(intrinsicDeviceScaleFactor());
1517
1518 if (Class gestureClass = NSClassFromString(@"NSImmediateActionGestureRecognizer")) {
1519 m_immediateActionGestureRecognizer = adoptNS([(NSImmediateActionGestureRecognizer *)[gestureClass alloc] init]);
1520 m_immediateActionController = adoptNS([[WKImmediateActionController alloc] initWithPage:m_page.get() view:view viewImpl:*this recognizer:m_immediateActionGestureRecognizer.get()]);
1521 [m_immediateActionGestureRecognizer setDelegate:m_immediateActionController.get()];
1522 [m_immediateActionGestureRecognizer setDelaysPrimaryMouseButtonEvents:NO];
1523 }
1524
1525 m_page->setAddsVisitedLinks(processPool.historyClient().addsVisitedLinks());
1526
1527 m_page->initializeWebPage();
1528
1529 registerDraggedTypes();
1530
1531 view.wantsLayer = YES;
1532
1533 // Explicitly set the layer contents placement so AppKit will make sure that our layer has masksToBounds set to YES.
1534 view.layerContentsPlacement = NSViewLayerContentsPlacementTopLeft;
1535
1536#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
1537 m_page->setFullscreenClient(makeUnique<WebKit::FullscreenClient>(view));
1538#endif
1539
1540#if HAVE(NSSCROLLVIEW_SEPARATOR_TRACKING_ADAPTER)
1541 m_lastScrollViewFrame = scrollViewFrame();
1542#endif
1543
1544 WebProcessPool::statistics().wkViewCount++;
1545}

1675
1676bool WebViewImpl::becomeFirstResponder()
1677{
1678 ASSERT(hasProcessPrivilege(ProcessPrivilege::CanCommunicateWithWindowServer));
1679 // If we just became first responder again, there is no need to do anything,
1680 // since resignFirstResponder has correctly detected this situation.
1681 if (m_willBecomeFirstResponderAgain) {
1682 m_willBecomeFirstResponderAgain = false;
1683 return true;
1684 }
1685
1686 NSSelectionDirection direction = [[m_view window] keyViewSelectionDirection];
1687
1688 m_inBecomeFirstResponder = true;
1689
1690 updateSecureInputState();
1691 m_page->activityStateDidChange(WebCore::ActivityState::IsFocused);
1692 // Restore the selection in the editable region if resigning first responder cleared selection.
1693 m_page->restoreSelectionInFocusedEditableElement();
1694
1695 m_inBecomeFirstResponder = false;
1696
1697#if HAVE(TOUCH_BAR)
1698 updateTouchBar();
1699#endif
1700
1701 if (direction != NSDirectSelection) {
1702 NSEvent *event = [NSApp currentEvent];
1703 NSEvent *keyboardEvent = nil;
1704 if ([event type] == NSEventTypeKeyDown || [event type] == NSEventTypeKeyUp)
1705 keyboardEvent = event;
1706 m_page->setInitialFocus(direction == NSSelectingNext, keyboardEvent != nil, NativeWebKeyboardEvent(keyboardEvent, false, false, { }), [] { });
1707 }
1708 return true;
1709}
1710
1711bool WebViewImpl::resignFirstResponder()
1712{
1713 // Predict the case where we are losing first responder status only to
1714 // gain it back again. We want resignFirstResponder to do nothing in that case.
1715 id nextResponder = [[m_view window] _newFirstResponderAfterResigning];
1716
1717 // FIXME: This will probably need to change once WKWebView doesn't contain a WKView.
1718 if ([nextResponder isKindOfClass:[WKWebView class]] && [m_view superview] == nextResponder) {
1719 m_willBecomeFirstResponderAgain = true;
1720 return true;
1721 }
1722
1723 m_willBecomeFirstResponderAgain = false;
1724 m_inResignFirstResponder = true;
1725
1726 m_page->confirmCompositionAsync();
1727
1728 notifyInputContextAboutDiscardedComposition();
1729
1730 resetSecureInputState();
1731
1732 if (!m_page->maintainsInactiveSelection())
1733 m_page->clearSelection();
1734
1735 m_page->activityStateDidChange(WebCore::ActivityState::IsFocused);
1736
1737 m_inResignFirstResponder = false;
1738
1739 return true;
1740}
1741
1742void WebViewImpl::takeFocus(WebCore::FocusDirection direction)
1743{
1744 NSView *webView = m_view.getAutoreleased();
1745
1746 if (direction == WebCore::FocusDirection::Forward) {
1747 // Since we're trying to move focus out of m_webView, and because
1748 // m_webView may contain subviews within it, we ask it for the next key
1749 // view of the last view in its key view loop. This makes m_webView
1750 // behave as if it had no subviews, which is the behavior we want.
1751 [webView.window selectKeyViewFollowingView:[webView _findLastViewInKeyViewLoop]];
1752 } else
1753 [webView.window selectKeyViewPrecedingView:webView];
1754}

1756void WebViewImpl::showSafeBrowsingWarning(const SafeBrowsingWarning& warning, CompletionHandler<void(Variant<ContinueUnsafeLoad, URL>&&)>&& completionHandler)
1757{
1758 if (!m_view)
1759 return completionHandler(ContinueUnsafeLoad::Yes);
1760
1761 m_safeBrowsingWarning = adoptNS([[WKSafeBrowsingWarning alloc] initWithFrame:[m_view bounds] safeBrowsingWarning:warning completionHandler:[weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)] (auto&& result) mutable {
1762 completionHandler(WTFMove(result));
1763 if (!weakThis)
1764 return;
1765 bool navigatesFrame = WTF::switchOn(result,
1766 [] (ContinueUnsafeLoad continueUnsafeLoad) { return continueUnsafeLoad == ContinueUnsafeLoad::Yes; },
1767 [] (const URL&) { return true; }
1768 );
1769 bool forMainFrameNavigation = [weakThis->m_safeBrowsingWarning forMainFrameNavigation];
1770 if (navigatesFrame && forMainFrameNavigation) {
1771 // The safe browsing warning will be hidden once the next page is shown.
1772 return;
1773 }
1774 if (!navigatesFrame && weakThis->m_safeBrowsingWarning && !forMainFrameNavigation) {
1775 weakThis->m_page->goBack();
1776 return;
1777 }
1778 [std::exchange(weakThis->m_safeBrowsingWarning, nullptr) removeFromSuperview];
1779 }]);
1780 [m_view addSubview:m_safeBrowsingWarning.get()];
1781}
1782
1783void WebViewImpl::clearSafeBrowsingWarning()
1784{
1785 [std::exchange(m_safeBrowsingWarning, nullptr) removeFromSuperview];
1786}
1787
1788void WebViewImpl::clearSafeBrowsingWarningIfForMainFrameNavigation()
1789{
1790 if ([m_safeBrowsingWarning forMainFrameNavigation])
1791 clearSafeBrowsingWarning();
1792}

1897void WebViewImpl::updateWindowAndViewFrames()
1898{
1899 if (clipsToVisibleRect())
1900 updateViewExposedRect();
1901
1902#if HAVE(NSSCROLLVIEW_SEPARATOR_TRACKING_ADAPTER)
1903 NSRect scrollViewFrame = this->scrollViewFrame();
1904 if (!NSEqualRects(m_lastScrollViewFrame, scrollViewFrame)) {
1905 m_lastScrollViewFrame = scrollViewFrame;
1906 [m_view didChangeValueForKey:@"scrollViewFrame"];
1907 }
1908
1909 updateTitlebarAdjacencyState();
1910#endif
1911
1912 if (m_didScheduleWindowAndViewFrameUpdate)
1913 return;
1914
1915 m_didScheduleWindowAndViewFrameUpdate = true;
1916
1917 RunLoop::main().dispatch([weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this)] {
1918 if (!weakThis)
1919 return;
1920
1921 weakThis->m_didScheduleWindowAndViewFrameUpdate = false;
1922
1923 NSRect viewFrameInWindowCoordinates = NSZeroRect;
1924 NSPoint accessibilityPosition = NSZeroPoint;
1925
1926 if (weakThis->m_needsViewFrameInWindowCoordinates)
1927 viewFrameInWindowCoordinates = [weakThis->m_view convertRect:[weakThis->m_view frame] toView:nil];
1928
1929 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_BEGIN
1930 if (WebCore::AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled())
1931 accessibilityPosition = [[weakThis->m_view accessibilityAttributeValue:NSAccessibilityPositionAttribute] pointValue];
1932 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_END
1933

2178bool WebViewImpl::supportsArbitraryLayoutModes() const
2179{
2180 if ([m_fullScreenWindowController isFullScreen])
2181 return false;
2182
2183 WebFrameProxy* frame = m_page->mainFrame();
2184 if (!frame)
2185 return true;
2186
2187 // If we have a plugin document in the main frame, avoid using custom WKLayoutModes
2188 // and fall back to the defaults, because there's a good chance that it won't work (e.g. with PDFPlugin).
2189 if (frame->containsPluginDocument())
2190 return false;
2191
2192 return true;
2193}
2194
2195void WebViewImpl::updateSupportsArbitraryLayoutModes()
2196{
2197 if (!supportsArbitraryLayoutModes()) {
2198 WKLayoutMode oldRequestedLayoutMode = m_lastRequestedLayoutMode;
2199 CGFloat oldRequestedViewScale = m_lastRequestedViewScale;
2200 CGSize oldRequestedFixedLayoutSize = m_lastRequestedFixedLayoutSize;
2201 setViewScale(1);
2202 setLayoutMode(kWKLayoutModeViewSize);
2203 setFixedLayoutSize(CGSizeZero);
2204
2205 // The 'last requested' parameters will have been overwritten by setting them above, but we don't
2206 // want this to count as a request (only changes from the client count), so reset them.
2207 m_lastRequestedLayoutMode = oldRequestedLayoutMode;
2208 m_lastRequestedViewScale = oldRequestedViewScale;
2209 m_lastRequestedFixedLayoutSize = oldRequestedFixedLayoutSize;
2210 } else if (m_lastRequestedLayoutMode != [m_layoutStrategy layoutMode]) {
2211 setViewScale(m_lastRequestedViewScale);
2212 setLayoutMode(m_lastRequestedLayoutMode);
2213 setFixedLayoutSize(m_lastRequestedFixedLayoutSize);
2214 }
2215}

2350bool WebViewImpl::acceptsFirstMouse(NSEvent *event)
2351{
2352 if (!mightBeginDragWhileInactive() && !mightBeginScrollWhileInactive())
2353 return false;
2354
2355 // There's a chance that responding to this event will run a nested event loop, and
2356 // fetching a new event might release the old one. Retaining and then autoreleasing
2357 // the current event prevents that from causing a problem inside WebKit or AppKit code.
2358 retainPtr(event).autorelease();
2359
2360 if (![m_view hitTest:event.locationInWindow])
2361 return false;
2362
2363 setLastMouseDownEvent(event);
2364 bool result = m_page->acceptsFirstMouse(event.eventNumber, WebEventFactory::createWebMouseEvent(event, m_lastPressureEvent.get(), m_view.getAutoreleased()));
2365 setLastMouseDownEvent(nil);
2366 return result;
2367}
2368
2369bool WebViewImpl::shouldDelayWindowOrderingForEvent(NSEvent *event)
2370{
2371 if (!mightBeginDragWhileInactive())
2372 return false;
2373
2374 // There's a chance that responding to this event will run a nested event loop, and
2375 // fetching a new event might release the old one. Retaining and then autoreleasing
2376 // the current event prevents that from causing a problem inside WebKit or AppKit code.
2377 retainPtr(event).autorelease();
2378
2379 if (![m_view hitTest:event.locationInWindow])
2380 return false;
2381
2382 setLastMouseDownEvent(event);
2383 bool result = m_page->shouldDelayWindowOrderingForEvent(WebEventFactory::createWebMouseEvent(event, m_lastPressureEvent.get(), m_view.getAutoreleased()));
2384 setLastMouseDownEvent(nil);
2385 return result;
2386}

2395void WebViewImpl::viewWillMoveToWindowImpl(NSWindow *window)
2396{
2397 // If we're in the middle of preparing to move to a window, we should only be moved to that window.
2398 ASSERT(!m_targetWindowForMovePreparation || (m_targetWindowForMovePreparation == window));
2399
2400 NSWindow *currentWindow = [m_view window];
2401 if (window == currentWindow)
2402 return;
2403
2404 clearAllEditCommands();
2405
2406 NSWindow *stopObservingWindow = m_targetWindowForMovePreparation ? m_targetWindowForMovePreparation.get() : [m_view window];
2407 [m_windowVisibilityObserver stopObserving:stopObservingWindow];
2408 [m_windowVisibilityObserver startObserving:window];
2409
2410#if HAVE(NSSCROLLVIEW_SEPARATOR_TRACKING_ADAPTER)
2411 if (m_isRegisteredScrollViewSeparatorTrackingAdapter) {
2412 [currentWindow unregisterScrollViewSeparatorTrackingAdapter:(NSObject<NSScrollViewSeparatorTrackingAdapter> *)m_view.get().get()];
2413 m_isRegisteredScrollViewSeparatorTrackingAdapter = false;
2414 }
2415#endif
2416}

2421 m_targetWindowForMovePreparation = nil;
2422}
2423
2424void WebViewImpl::viewDidMoveToWindow()
2425{
2426 NSWindow *window = m_targetWindowForMovePreparation ? m_targetWindowForMovePreparation.get() : [m_view window];
2427
2428 LOG(ActivityState, "WebViewImpl %p viewDidMoveToWindow %p", this, window);
2429
2430 if (window) {
2431 windowDidChangeScreen();
2432
2433 OptionSet<WebCore::ActivityState::Flag> activityStateChanges { WebCore::ActivityState::WindowIsActive, WebCore::ActivityState::IsVisible };
2434 if (m_shouldDeferViewInWindowChanges)
2435 m_viewInWindowChangeWasDeferred = true;
2436 else
2437 activityStateChanges.add(WebCore::ActivityState::IsInWindow);
2438 m_page->activityStateDidChange(activityStateChanges);
2439
2440 updateWindowAndViewFrames();
2441
2442 // FIXME(135509) This call becomes unnecessary once 135509 is fixed; remove.
2443 m_page->layerHostingModeDidChange();
2444
2445 if (!m_flagsChangedEventMonitor) {
2446 auto weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this);
2447 m_flagsChangedEventMonitor = [NSEvent addLocalMonitorForEventsMatchingMask:NSEventMaskFlagsChanged handler:[weakThis] (NSEvent *flagsChangedEvent) {
2448 if (weakThis)
2449 weakThis->postFakeMouseMovedEventForFlagsChangedEvent(flagsChangedEvent);
2450 return flagsChangedEvent;
2451 }];
2452 }
2453
2454 accessibilityRegisterUIProcessTokens();
2455
2456 if (m_immediateActionGestureRecognizer && ![[m_view gestureRecognizers] containsObject:m_immediateActionGestureRecognizer.get()] && !m_ignoresNonWheelEvents && m_allowsLinkPreview)
2457 [m_view addGestureRecognizer:m_immediateActionGestureRecognizer.get()];
2458 } else {
2459 OptionSet<WebCore::ActivityState::Flag> activityStateChanges { WebCore::ActivityState::WindowIsActive, WebCore::ActivityState::IsVisible };
2460 if (m_shouldDeferViewInWindowChanges)
2461 m_viewInWindowChangeWasDeferred = true;
2462 else
2463 activityStateChanges.add(WebCore::ActivityState::IsInWindow);
2464 m_page->activityStateDidChange(activityStateChanges);
2465
2466 [NSEvent removeMonitor:m_flagsChangedEventMonitor];
2467 m_flagsChangedEventMonitor = nil;
2468
2469 dismissContentRelativeChildWindowsWithAnimation(false);
2470 m_page->closeSharedPreviewPanelIfNecessary();
2471
2472 if (m_immediateActionGestureRecognizer) {
2473 // Work around <rdar://problem/22646404> by explicitly cancelling the animation.
2474 cancelImmediateActionAnimation();
2475 [m_view removeGestureRecognizer:m_immediateActionGestureRecognizer.get()];
2476 }
2477 }
2478
2479 m_page->setIntrinsicDeviceScaleFactor(intrinsicDeviceScaleFactor());
2480 m_page->webViewDidMoveToWindow();
2481}

2541void WebViewImpl::updateTitlebarAdjacencyState()
2542{
2543 NSWindow *window = [m_view window];
2544 bool visible = ![m_view isHiddenOrHasHiddenAncestor];
2545 CGFloat topOfWindowContentLayoutRectInSelf = NSMinY([m_view convertRect:[window contentLayoutRect] fromView:nil]);
2546 bool topOfWindowContentLayoutRectAdjacent = NSMinY([m_view bounds]) <= topOfWindowContentLayoutRectInSelf;
2547
2548 bool shouldRegister = topOfWindowContentLayoutRectAdjacent && visible && [[m_view effectiveAppearance] _usesMetricsAppearance];
2549
2550 if (shouldRegister && !m_isRegisteredScrollViewSeparatorTrackingAdapter && [m_view conformsToProtocol:@protocol(NSScrollViewSeparatorTrackingAdapter)]) {
2551 m_isRegisteredScrollViewSeparatorTrackingAdapter = [window registerScrollViewSeparatorTrackingAdapter:(NSObject<NSScrollViewSeparatorTrackingAdapter> *)m_view.get().get()];
2552 } else if (!shouldRegister && m_isRegisteredScrollViewSeparatorTrackingAdapter) {
2553 [window unregisterScrollViewSeparatorTrackingAdapter:(NSObject<NSScrollViewSeparatorTrackingAdapter> *)m_view.get().get()];
2554 m_isRegisteredScrollViewSeparatorTrackingAdapter = false;
2555 }
2556}

2797bool WebViewImpl::tryHandlePluginComplexTextInputKeyDown(NSEvent *event)
2798{
2799 if (!m_pluginComplexTextInputIdentifier || m_pluginComplexTextInputState == PluginComplexTextInputDisabled)
2800 return NO;
2801
2802 // Check if the text input window has been dismissed and let the plug-in process know.
2803 // This is only valid with the updated Cocoa text input spec.
2804 disableComplexTextInputIfNecessary();
2805
2806 // Try feeding the keyboard event directly to the plug-in.
2807 if (m_pluginComplexTextInputState == PluginComplexTextInputEnabledLegacy)
2808 return handlePluginComplexTextInputKeyDown(event);
2809
2810 return NO;

2813void WebViewImpl::pluginFocusOrWindowFocusChanged(bool pluginHasFocusAndWindowHasFocus, uint64_t pluginComplexTextInputIdentifier)
2814{
2815 ASSERT(hasProcessPrivilege(ProcessPrivilege::CanCommunicateWithWindowServer));
2816 bool inputSourceChanged = !!m_pluginComplexTextInputIdentifier;
2817
2818 if (pluginHasFocusAndWindowHasFocus) {
2819 // Check if we're already allowing text input for this plug-in.
2820 if (pluginComplexTextInputIdentifier == m_pluginComplexTextInputIdentifier)
2821 return;
2822
2823 m_pluginComplexTextInputIdentifier = pluginComplexTextInputIdentifier;
2824
2825 } else {
2826 // Check if we got a request to unfocus a plug-in that isn't focused.
2827 if (pluginComplexTextInputIdentifier != m_pluginComplexTextInputIdentifier)
2828 return;
2829
2830 m_pluginComplexTextInputIdentifier = 0;
2831 }
2832
2833 if (inputSourceChanged) {
2834 // The input source changed; discard any entered text.
2835 [[WKTextInputWindowController sharedTextInputWindowController] unmarkText];
2836 }
2837
2838 // This will force the current input context to be updated to its correct value.
2839 [NSApp updateWindows];
2840}

2848 if (m_pluginComplexTextInputState == PluginComplexTextInputEnabledLegacy)
2849 return NO;
2850

2931typedef HashMap<SEL, String> SelectorNameMap;
2932
2933// Map selectors into Editor command names.
2934// This is not needed for any selectors that have the same name as the Editor command.
2935static const SelectorNameMap& selectorExceptionMap()
2936{
2937 static NeverDestroyed<SelectorNameMap> map;
2938
2939 struct SelectorAndCommandName {
2940 SEL selector;
2941 ASCIILiteral commandName;
2942 };
2943
2944 static const SelectorAndCommandName names[] = {
2945 { @selector(insertNewlineIgnoringFieldEditor:), "InsertNewline"_s },
2946 { @selector(insertParagraphSeparator:), "InsertNewline"_s },
2947 { @selector(insertTabIgnoringFieldEditor:), "InsertTab"_s },
2948 { @selector(pageDown:), "MovePageDown"_s },
2949 { @selector(pageDownAndModifySelection:), "MovePageDownAndModifySelection"_s },
2950 { @selector(pageUp:), "MovePageUp"_s },
2951 { @selector(pageUpAndModifySelection:), "MovePageUpAndModifySelection"_s },
2952 { @selector(scrollPageDown:), "ScrollPageForward"_s },
2953 { @selector(scrollPageUp:), "ScrollPageBackward"_s },
2954 { @selector(_pasteAsQuotation:), "PasteAsQuotation"_s },
2955 };
2956
2957 for (auto& name : names)
2958 map.get().add(name.selector, name.commandName);
2959
2960 return map;
2961}
2962
2963static String commandNameForSelector(SEL selector)
2964{
2965 // Check the exception map first.
2966 static const SelectorNameMap& exceptionMap = selectorExceptionMap();
2967 SelectorNameMap::const_iterator it = exceptionMap.find(selector);
2968 if (it != exceptionMap.end())
2969 return it->value;
2970
2971 // Remove the trailing colon.
2972 // No need to capitalize the command name since Editor command names are
2973 // not case sensitive.
2974 const char* selectorName = sel_getName(selector);
2975 size_t selectorNameLength = strlen(selectorName);
2976 if (selectorNameLength < 2 || selectorName[selectorNameLength - 1] != ':')
2977 return String();
2978 return String(selectorName, selectorNameLength - 1);
2979}

2981bool WebViewImpl::executeSavedCommandBySelector(SEL selector)
2982{
2983 LOG(TextInput, "Executing previously saved command %s", sel_getName(selector));
2984 // The sink does two things: 1) Tells us if the responder went unhandled, and
2985 // 2) prevents any NSBeep; we don't ever want to beep here.
2986 RetainPtr<WKResponderChainSink> sink = adoptNS([[WKResponderChainSink alloc] initWithResponderChain:m_view.getAutoreleased()]);
2987 [m_view _web_superDoCommandBySelector:selector];
2988 [sink detach];
2989 return ![sink didReceiveUnhandledCommand];

3033id WebViewImpl::validRequestorForSendAndReturnTypes(NSString *sendType, NSString *returnType)
3034{
3035 EditorState editorState = m_page->editorState();
3036 bool isValidSendType = false;
3037
3038 if (sendType && !editorState.selectionIsNone) {
3039 if (editorState.isInPlugin)
3040 isValidSendType = [sendType isEqualToString:WebCore::legacyStringPasteboardType()];
3041 else
3042 isValidSendType = [PasteboardTypes::forSelection() containsObject:sendType];
3043 }
3044
3045 bool isValidReturnType = false;
3046 if (!returnType)
3047 isValidReturnType = true;
3048 else if ([PasteboardTypes::forEditing() containsObject:returnType] && editorState.isContentEditable) {
3049 // We can insert strings in any editable context. We can insert other types, like images, only in rich edit contexts.
3050 isValidReturnType = editorState.isContentRichlyEditable || [returnType isEqualToString:WebCore::legacyStringPasteboardType()];
3051 }
3052 if (isValidSendType && isValidReturnType)
3053 return m_view.getAutoreleased();
3054 return [[m_view nextResponder] validRequestorForSendType:sendType returnType:returnType];
3055}

3209 [menuItem setTitle:WebCore::contextMenuItemTagShowSpellingPanel(![[[NSSpellChecker sharedSpellChecker] spellingPanel] isVisible])];
3210 return m_page->editorState().isContentEditable;
3211 }
3212
3213 if (action == @selector(checkSpelling:) || action == @selector(changeSpelling:))
3214 return m_page->editorState().isContentEditable;
3215
3216 if (action == @selector(toggleContinuousSpellChecking:)) {
3217 bool enabled = TextChecker::isContinuousSpellCheckingAllowed();
3218 bool checked = enabled && TextChecker::state().isContinuousSpellCheckingEnabled;
3219 [menuItem(item) setState:checked ? NSControlStateValueOn : NSControlStateValueOff];
3220 return enabled;
3221 }
3222
3223 if (action == @selector(toggleGrammarChecking:)) {
3224 bool checked = TextChecker::state().isGrammarCheckingEnabled;
3225 [menuItem(item) setState:checked ? NSControlStateValueOn : NSControlStateValueOff];
3226 return true;
3227 }
3228
3229 if (action == @selector(toggleAutomaticSpellingCorrection:)) {
3230 auto& editorState = m_page->editorState();
3231 bool enable = editorState.isContentEditable && (editorState.isMissingPostLayoutData || editorState.postLayoutData().canEnableAutomaticSpellingCorrection);
3232 menuItem(item).state = TextChecker::state().isAutomaticSpellingCorrectionEnabled && enable ? NSControlStateValueOn : NSControlStateValueOff;
3233 return enable;
3234 }
3235
3236 if (action == @selector(orderFrontSubstitutionsPanel:)) {
3237 if (NSMenuItem *menuItem = WebKit::menuItem(item))
3238 [menuItem setTitle:WebCore::contextMenuItemTagShowSubstitutions(![[[NSSpellChecker sharedSpellChecker] substitutionsPanel] isVisible])];
3239 return m_page->editorState().isContentEditable;
3240 }
3241
3242 if (action == @selector(toggleSmartInsertDelete:)) {
3243 bool checked = m_page->isSmartInsertDeleteEnabled();
3244 [menuItem(item) setState:checked ? NSControlStateValueOn : NSControlStateValueOff];
3245 return m_page->editorState().isContentEditable;
3246 }
3247
3248 if (action == @selector(toggleAutomaticQuoteSubstitution:)) {
3249 bool checked = TextChecker::state().isAutomaticQuoteSubstitutionEnabled;
3250 [menuItem(item) setState:checked ? NSControlStateValueOn : NSControlStateValueOff];
3251 return m_page->editorState().isContentEditable;
3252 }
3253
3254 if (action == @selector(toggleAutomaticDashSubstitution:)) {
3255 bool checked = TextChecker::state().isAutomaticDashSubstitutionEnabled;
3256 [menuItem(item) setState:checked ? NSControlStateValueOn : NSControlStateValueOff];
3257 return m_page->editorState().isContentEditable;
3258 }
3259
3260 if (action == @selector(toggleAutomaticLinkDetection:)) {
3261 bool checked = TextChecker::state().isAutomaticLinkDetectionEnabled;
3262 [menuItem(item) setState:checked ? NSControlStateValueOn : NSControlStateValueOff];
3263 return m_page->editorState().isContentEditable;
3264 }
3265
3266 if (action == @selector(toggleAutomaticTextReplacement:)) {
3267 bool checked = TextChecker::state().isAutomaticTextReplacementEnabled;
3268 [menuItem(item) setState:checked ? NSControlStateValueOn : NSControlStateValueOff];
3269 return m_page->editorState().isContentEditable;
3270 }
3271
3272 if (action == @selector(uppercaseWord:) || action == @selector(lowercaseWord:) || action == @selector(capitalizeWord:))
3273 return m_page->editorState().selectionIsRange && m_page->editorState().isContentEditable;
3274
3275 if (action == @selector(stopSpeaking:))
3276 return [NSApp isSpeaking];
3277
3278 // The centerSelectionInVisibleArea: selector is enabled if there's a selection range or if there's an insertion point in an editable area.
3279 if (action == @selector(centerSelectionInVisibleArea:))
3280 return m_page->editorState().selectionIsRange || (m_page->editorState().isContentEditable && !m_page->editorState().selectionIsNone);
3281
3282 // Next, handle editor commands. Start by returning true for anything that is not an editor command.
3283 // Returning true is the default thing to do in an AppKit validate method for any selector that is not recognized.
3284 String commandName = commandNameForSelector([item action]);
3285 if (!WebCore::Editor::commandIsSupportedFromMenuOrKeyBinding(commandName))
3286 return true;
3287
3288 // Add this item to the vector of items for a given command that are awaiting validation.
3289 ValidationMap::AddResult addResult = m_validationMap.add(commandName, ValidationVector());
3290 addResult.iterator->value.append(item);
3291 if (addResult.isNewEntry) {
3292 // If we are not already awaiting validation for this command, start the asynchronous validation process.
3293 // FIXME: Theoretically, there is a race here; when we get the answer it might be old, from a previous time
3294 // we asked for the same command; there is no guarantee the answer is still valid.
3295 m_page->validateCommand(commandName, [weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this), commandName](bool isEnabled, int32_t state) {
3296 if (!weakThis)
3297 return;
3298
3299 weakThis->setUserInterfaceItemState(commandName, isEnabled, state);
3300 });
3301 }
3302
3303 // Treat as enabled until we get the result back from the web process and _setUserInterfaceItemState is called.
3304 // FIXME <rdar://problem/8803459>: This means disabled items will flash enabled at first for a moment.
3305 // But returning NO here would be worse; that would make keyboard commands such as command-C fail.
3306 return true;
3307}

3309void WebViewImpl::setUserInterfaceItemState(NSString *commandName, bool enabled, int state)
3310{
3311 ValidationVector items = m_validationMap.take(commandName);
3312 for (auto& item : items) {
3313 [menuItem(item.get()) setState:state];
3314 [menuItem(item.get()) setEnabled:enabled];
3315 [toolbarItem(item.get()) setEnabled:enabled];
3316 // FIXME <rdar://problem/8803392>: If the item is neither a menu nor toolbar item, it will be left enabled.
3317 }
3318}

3529void WebViewImpl::requestCandidatesForSelectionIfNeeded()
3530{
3531 if (!shouldRequestCandidates())
3532 return;
3533
3534 const EditorState& editorState = m_page->editorState();
3535 if (!editorState.isContentEditable)
3536 return;
3537
3538 if (editorState.isMissingPostLayoutData)
3539 return;
3540
3541 auto& postLayoutData = editorState.postLayoutData();
3542 m_lastStringForCandidateRequest = postLayoutData.stringForCandidateRequest;
3543
3544 NSRange selectedRange = NSMakeRange(postLayoutData.candidateRequestStartPosition, postLayoutData.selectedTextLength);
3545 NSTextCheckingTypes checkingTypes = NSTextCheckingTypeSpelling | NSTextCheckingTypeReplacement | NSTextCheckingTypeCorrection;
3546 auto weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this);
3547 m_lastCandidateRequestSequenceNumber = [[NSSpellChecker sharedSpellChecker] requestCandidatesForSelectedRange:selectedRange inString:postLayoutData.paragraphContextForCandidateRequest types:checkingTypes options:nil inSpellDocumentWithTag:spellCheckerDocumentTag() completionHandler:[weakThis](NSInteger sequenceNumber, NSArray<NSTextCheckingResult *> *candidates) {
3548 RunLoop::main().dispatch([weakThis, sequenceNumber, candidates = retainPtr(candidates)] {
3549 if (!weakThis)
3550 return;
3551 weakThis->handleRequestedCandidates(sequenceNumber, candidates.get());
3552 });
3553 }];
3554}
3555
3556void WebViewImpl::handleRequestedCandidates(NSInteger sequenceNumber, NSArray<NSTextCheckingResult *> *candidates)
3557{
3558 if (!shouldRequestCandidates())
3559 return;
3560
3561 if (m_lastCandidateRequestSequenceNumber != sequenceNumber)
3562 return;
3563
3564 const EditorState& editorState = m_page->editorState();
3565 if (!editorState.isContentEditable)
3566 return;
3567
3568 // FIXME: It's pretty lame that we have to depend on the most recent EditorState having post layout data,
3569 // and that we just bail if it is missing.
3570 if (editorState.isMissingPostLayoutData)
3571 return;
3572
3573 auto& postLayoutData = editorState.postLayoutData();
3574 if (m_lastStringForCandidateRequest != postLayoutData.stringForCandidateRequest)
3575 return;
3576
3577#if HAVE(TOUCH_BAR)
3578 NSRange selectedRange = NSMakeRange(postLayoutData.candidateRequestStartPosition, postLayoutData.selectedTextLength);
3579 WebCore::IntRect offsetSelectionRect = postLayoutData.selectionBoundingRect;
3580 offsetSelectionRect.move(0, offsetSelectionRect.height());
3581
3582 [candidateListTouchBarItem() setCandidates:candidates forSelectedRange:selectedRange inString:postLayoutData.paragraphContextForCandidateRequest rect:offsetSelectionRect view:m_view.getAutoreleased() completionHandler:nil];
3583#else
3584 UNUSED_PARAM(candidates);
3585#endif
3586}

3588static constexpr WebCore::TextCheckingType coreTextCheckingType(NSTextCheckingType type)
3589{
3590 switch (type) {
3591 case NSTextCheckingTypeCorrection:
3592 return WebCore::TextCheckingType::Correction;
3593 case NSTextCheckingTypeReplacement:
3594 return WebCore::TextCheckingType::Replacement;
3595 case NSTextCheckingTypeSpelling:
3596 return WebCore::TextCheckingType::Spelling;
3597 default:
3598 return WebCore::TextCheckingType::None;
3599 }
3600}

3602static WebCore::TextCheckingResult textCheckingResultFromNSTextCheckingResult(NSTextCheckingResult *nsResult)
3603{
3604 WebCore::TextCheckingResult result;
3605 result.type = coreTextCheckingType(nsResult.resultType);
3606 result.range = nsResult.range;
3607 result.replacement = nsResult.replacementString;
3608 return result;

3611void WebViewImpl::handleAcceptedCandidate(NSTextCheckingResult *acceptedCandidate)
3612{
3613 const EditorState& editorState = m_page->editorState();
3614 if (!editorState.isContentEditable)
3615 return;
3616
3617 // FIXME: It's pretty lame that we have to depend on the most recent EditorState having post layout data,
3618 // and that we just bail if it is missing.
3619 if (editorState.isMissingPostLayoutData)
3620 return;
3621
3622 auto& postLayoutData = editorState.postLayoutData();
3623 if (m_lastStringForCandidateRequest != postLayoutData.stringForCandidateRequest)
3624 return;
3625
3626 m_isHandlingAcceptedCandidate = true;
3627 NSRange range = [acceptedCandidate range];
3628 if (acceptedCandidate.replacementString && [acceptedCandidate.replacementString length] > 0) {
3629 NSRange replacedRange = NSMakeRange(range.location, [acceptedCandidate.replacementString length]);
3630 NSRange softSpaceRange = NSMakeRange(NSMaxRange(replacedRange) - 1, 1);
3631 if ([acceptedCandidate.replacementString hasSuffix:@" "])
3632 m_softSpaceRange = softSpaceRange;
3633 }
3634
3635 m_page->handleAcceptedCandidate(textCheckingResultFromNSTextCheckingResult(acceptedCandidate));
3636}

3825void WebViewImpl::updateRemoteAccessibilityRegistration(bool registerProcess)
3826{
3827 // When the tree is connected/disconnected, the remote accessibility registration
3828 // needs to be updated with the pid of the remote process. If the process is going
3829 // away, that information is not present in WebProcess
3830 pid_t pid = 0;
3831 if (registerProcess)
3832 pid = m_page->process().processIdentifier();
3833 else if (!registerProcess) {
3834 pid = [m_remoteAccessibilityChild processIdentifier];
3835 m_remoteAccessibilityChild = nil;
3836 }
3837 if (!pid)
3838 return;
3839
3840 if (registerProcess)
3841 [NSAccessibilityRemoteUIElement registerRemoteUIProcessIdentifier:pid];
3842 else
3843 [NSAccessibilityRemoteUIElement unregisterRemoteUIProcessIdentifier:pid];
3844}

3853 m_page->registerUIProcessAccessibilityTokens(elementToken, windowToken);
3854}

3878id WebViewImpl::accessibilityAttributeValue(NSString *attribute, id parameter)
3879{
3880 enableAccessibilityIfNecessary();
3881
3882 if ([attribute isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityChildrenAttribute]) {
3883
3884 id child = nil;
3885 if (m_safeBrowsingWarning)
3886 child = m_safeBrowsingWarning.get();
3887 else if (m_remoteAccessibilityChild)
3888 child = m_remoteAccessibilityChild.get();
3889
3890 if (!child)
3891 return nil;
3892 return @[child];
3893 }
3894 if ([attribute isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityRoleAttribute])
3895 return NSAccessibilityGroupRole;
3896 if ([attribute isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityRoleDescriptionAttribute])
3897 return NSAccessibilityRoleDescription(NSAccessibilityGroupRole, nil);
3898 if ([attribute isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityParentAttribute])
3899 return NSAccessibilityUnignoredAncestor([m_view superview]);
3900 if ([attribute isEqualToString:NSAccessibilityEnabledAttribute])
3901 return @YES;
3902
3903 if ([attribute isEqualToString:@"AXConvertRelativeFrame"]) {
3904 if ([parameter isKindOfClass:[NSValue class]]) {
3905 NSRect rect = [(NSValue *)parameter rectValue];
3906 return [NSValue valueWithRect:m_pageClient->rootViewToScreen(WebCore::IntRect(rect))];
3907 }
3908 }
3909
3910 return [m_view _web_superAccessibilityAttributeValue:attribute];
3911}

4031void WebViewImpl::enterAcceleratedCompositingWithRootLayer(CALayer *rootLayer)
4032{
4033 // This is the process-swap case. We add the new layer behind the existing root layer and mark it as hidden.
4034 // This way, the new layer gets accelerated compositing but won't be visible until
4035 // setAcceleratedCompositingRootLayer() is called by didFirstLayerFlush(), in order to prevent flashing.
4036 if (m_rootLayer && rootLayer && m_rootLayer != rootLayer) {
4037 if (m_thumbnailView)
4038 return;
4039
4040 [rootLayer web_disableAllActions];
4041
4042 [CATransaction begin];
4043 [CATransaction setDisableActions:YES];
4044
4045 rootLayer.hidden = YES;
4046 [[m_layerHostingView layer] insertSublayer:rootLayer atIndex:0];
4047
4048 [CATransaction commit];
4049 return;
4050 }
4051
4052 setAcceleratedCompositingRootLayer(rootLayer);
4053}
4054
4055void WebViewImpl::setAcceleratedCompositingRootLayer(CALayer *rootLayer)
4056{
4057 [rootLayer web_disableAllActions];
4058
4059 m_rootLayer = rootLayer;
4060 rootLayer.hidden = NO;
4061
4062 if (m_thumbnailView) {
4063 updateThumbnailViewLayer();
4064 return;
4065 }
4066
4067 [CATransaction begin];
4068 [CATransaction setDisableActions:YES];
4069
4070 [m_layerHostingView layer].sublayers = rootLayer ? @[ rootLayer ] : nil;
4071
4072 [CATransaction commit];
4073}

4188static NSDragOperation kit(std::optional<WebCore::DragOperation> dragOperation)
4189{
4190 if (!dragOperation)
4191 return NSDragOperationNone;
4192
4193 switch (*dragOperation) {
4194 case WebCore::DragOperation::Copy:
4195 return NSDragOperationCopy;
4196 case WebCore::DragOperation::Link:
4197 return NSDragOperationLink;
4198 case WebCore::DragOperation::Generic:
4199 return NSDragOperationGeneric;
4200 case WebCore::DragOperation::Private:
4201 return NSDragOperationPrivate;
4202 case WebCore::DragOperation::Move:
4203 return NSDragOperationMove;
4204 case WebCore::DragOperation::Delete:
4205 return NSDragOperationDelete;
4206 }
4207
4208 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4209 return NSDragOperationNone;
4210}

4253
4254bool WebViewImpl::performDragOperation(id <NSDraggingInfo> draggingInfo)
4255{
4256 WebCore::IntPoint client([m_view convertPoint:draggingInfo.draggingLocation fromView:nil]);
4257 WebCore::IntPoint global(WebCore::globalPoint(draggingInfo.draggingLocation, [m_view window]));
4258 WebCore::DragData *dragData = new WebCore::DragData(draggingInfo, client, global, coreDragOperationMask(draggingInfo.draggingSourceOperationMask), applicationFlagsForDrag(m_view.getAutoreleased(), draggingInfo), WebCore::anyDragDestinationAction(), m_page->webPageID());
4259
4260 NSArray *types = draggingInfo.draggingPasteboard.types;
4261 SandboxExtension::Handle sandboxExtensionHandle;
4262 SandboxExtension::HandleArray sandboxExtensionForUpload;
4263
4264 if (![types containsObject:PasteboardTypes::WebArchivePboardType] && [types containsObject:WebCore::legacyFilesPromisePasteboardType()]) {
4265
4266 // FIXME: legacyFilesPromisePasteboardType() contains UTIs, not path names. Also, it's not
4267 // guaranteed that the count of UTIs equals the count of files, since some clients only write
4268 // unique UTIs.
4269 NSArray *files = [draggingInfo.draggingPasteboard propertyListForType:WebCore::legacyFilesPromisePasteboardType()];
4270 if (![files isKindOfClass:[NSArray class]]) {
4271 delete dragData;
4272 return false;
4273 }
4274
4275 NSString *dropDestinationPath = FileSystem::createTemporaryDirectory(@"WebKitDropDestination");
4276 if (!dropDestinationPath) {
4277 delete dragData;
4278 return false;
4279 }
4280
4281 size_t fileCount = files.count;
4282 Vector<String> *fileNames = new Vector<String>;
4283 NSURL *dropDestination = [NSURL fileURLWithPath:dropDestinationPath isDirectory:YES];
4284 String pasteboardName = draggingInfo.draggingPasteboard.name;
4285 [draggingInfo enumerateDraggingItemsWithOptions:0 forView:m_view.getAutoreleased() classes:@[[NSFilePromiseReceiver class]] searchOptions:@{ } usingBlock:^(NSDraggingItem *draggingItem, NSInteger idx, BOOL *stop) {
4286 NSFilePromiseReceiver *item = draggingItem.item;
4287 NSDictionary *options = @{ };
4288
4289 RetainPtr<NSOperationQueue> queue = adoptNS([NSOperationQueue new]);
4290 [item receivePromisedFilesAtDestination:dropDestination options:options operationQueue:queue.get() reader:^(NSURL *fileURL, NSError *errorOrNil) {
4291 if (errorOrNil)
4292 return;
4293
4294 RunLoop::main().dispatch([this, path = RetainPtr<NSString>(fileURL.path), fileNames, fileCount, dragData, pasteboardName] {
4295 fileNames->append(path.get());
4296 if (fileNames->size() == fileCount) {
4297 SandboxExtension::Handle sandboxExtensionHandle;
4298 SandboxExtension::HandleArray sandboxExtensionForUpload;
4299
4300 m_page->createSandboxExtensionsIfNeeded(*fileNames, sandboxExtensionHandle, sandboxExtensionForUpload);
4301 dragData->setFileNames(*fileNames);
4302 m_page->performDragOperation(*dragData, pasteboardName, WTFMove(sandboxExtensionHandle), WTFMove(sandboxExtensionForUpload));
4303 delete dragData;
4304 delete fileNames;
4305 }
4306 });
4307 }];
4308 }];
4309
4310 return true;
4311 }
4312
4313 if ([types containsObject:WebCore::legacyFilenamesPasteboardType()]) {
4314 NSArray *files = [draggingInfo.draggingPasteboard propertyListForType:WebCore::legacyFilenamesPasteboardType()];
4315 if (![files isKindOfClass:[NSArray class]]) {
4316 delete dragData;
4317 return false;
4318 }
4319
4320 m_page->createSandboxExtensionsIfNeeded(makeVector<String>(files), sandboxExtensionHandle, sandboxExtensionForUpload);
4321 }
4322
4323 String draggingPasteboardName = draggingInfo.draggingPasteboard.name;
4324 m_page->grantAccessToCurrentPasteboardData(draggingPasteboardName);
4325 m_page->performDragOperation(*dragData, draggingPasteboardName, WTFMove(sandboxExtensionHandle), WTFMove(sandboxExtensionForUpload));
4326 delete dragData;
4327
4328 return true;
4329}

4408
4409void WebViewImpl::startDrag(const WebCore::DragItem& item, const ShareableBitmap::Handle& dragImageHandle)
4410{
4411 auto dragImageAsBitmap = ShareableBitmap::create(dragImageHandle);
4412 if (!dragImageAsBitmap) {
4413 m_page->dragCancelled();
4414 return;
4415 }
4416
4417 auto dragCGImage = dragImageAsBitmap->makeCGImage();
4418 auto dragNSImage = adoptNS([[NSImage alloc] initWithCGImage:dragCGImage.get() size:dragImageAsBitmap->size()]);
4419
4420 WebCore::IntSize size([dragNSImage size]);
4421 size.scale(1.0 / m_page->deviceScaleFactor());
4422 [dragNSImage setSize:size];
4423
4424 // The call below could release the view.
4425 auto protector = m_view.get();
4426 auto clientDragLocation = item.dragLocationInWindowCoordinates;

4552static BOOL fileExists(NSString *path)
4553{
4554 struct stat statBuffer;
4555 return !lstat([path fileSystemRepresentation], &statBuffer);

4557
4558static NSString *pathWithUniqueFilenameForPath(NSString *path)
4559{
4560 // "Fix" the filename of the path.
4561 NSString *filename = filenameByFixingIllegalCharacters([path lastPathComponent]);
4562 path = [[path stringByDeletingLastPathComponent] stringByAppendingPathComponent:filename];
4563
4564 if (fileExists(path)) {
4565 // Don't overwrite existing file by appending "-n", "-n.ext" or "-n.ext.ext" to the filename.
4566 NSString *extensions = nil;
4567 NSString *pathWithoutExtensions;
4568 NSString *lastPathComponent = [path lastPathComponent];
4569 NSRange periodRange = [lastPathComponent rangeOfString:@"."];
4570
4571 if (periodRange.location == NSNotFound) {
4572 pathWithoutExtensions = path;
4573 } else {
4574 extensions = [lastPathComponent substringFromIndex:periodRange.location + 1];
4575 lastPathComponent = [lastPathComponent substringToIndex:periodRange.location];
4576 pathWithoutExtensions = [[path stringByDeletingLastPathComponent] stringByAppendingPathComponent:lastPathComponent];
4577 }
4578
4579 for (unsigned i = 1; ; i++) {
4580 NSString *pathWithAppendedNumber = [NSString stringWithFormat:@"%@-%d", pathWithoutExtensions, i];
4581 path = [extensions length] ? [pathWithAppendedNumber stringByAppendingPathExtension:extensions] : pathWithAppendedNumber;
4582 if (!fileExists(path))
4583 break;
4584 }
4585 }
4586
4587 return path;
4588}

4657static RetainPtr<CGImageRef> takeWindowSnapshot(CGSWindowID windowID, bool captureAtNominalResolution)
4658{
4659 CGSWindowCaptureOptions options = kCGSCaptureIgnoreGlobalClipShape;
4660 if (captureAtNominalResolution)
4661 options |= kCGSWindowCaptureNominalResolution;
4662 RetainPtr<CFArrayRef> windowSnapshotImages = adoptCF(CGSHWCaptureWindowList(CGSMainConnectionID(), &windowID, 1, options));
4663
4664 if (windowSnapshotImages && CFArrayGetCount(windowSnapshotImages.get()))
4665 return checked_cf_cast<CGImageRef>(CFArrayGetValueAtIndex(windowSnapshotImages.get(), 0));
4666
4667 // Fall back to the non-hardware capture path if we didn't get a snapshot
4668 // (which usually happens if the window is fully off-screen).
4669 CGWindowImageOption imageOptions = kCGWindowImageBoundsIgnoreFraming | kCGWindowImageShouldBeOpaque;
4670 if (captureAtNominalResolution)
4671 imageOptions |= kCGWindowImageNominalResolution;
4672 return adoptCF(CGWindowListCreateImage(CGRectNull, kCGWindowListOptionIncludingWindow, windowID, imageOptions));
4673}

4675RefPtr<ViewSnapshot> WebViewImpl::takeViewSnapshot()
4676{
4677 NSWindow *window = [m_view window];
4678
4679 CGSWindowID windowID = (CGSWindowID)window.windowNumber;
4680 if (!windowID || !window.isVisible)
4681 return nullptr;
4682
4683 RetainPtr<CGImageRef> windowSnapshotImage = takeWindowSnapshot(windowID, false);
4684 if (!windowSnapshotImage)
4685 return nullptr;
4686
4687 // Work around <rdar://problem/17084993>; re-request the snapshot at kCGWindowImageNominalResolution if it was captured at the wrong scale.
4688 CGFloat desiredSnapshotWidth = window.frame.size.width * window.screen.backingScaleFactor;
4689 if (CGImageGetWidth(windowSnapshotImage.get()) != desiredSnapshotWidth)
4690 windowSnapshotImage = takeWindowSnapshot(windowID, true);
4691
4692 if (!windowSnapshotImage)
4693 return nullptr;
4694
4695 ViewGestureController& gestureController = ensureGestureController();
4696
4697 NSRect windowCaptureRect;
4698 WebCore::FloatRect boundsForCustomSwipeViews = gestureController.windowRelativeBoundsForCustomSwipeViews();
4699 if (!boundsForCustomSwipeViews.isEmpty())
4700 windowCaptureRect = boundsForCustomSwipeViews;
4701 else {
4702 NSRect unobscuredBounds = [m_view bounds];
4703 float topContentInset = m_page->topContentInset();
4704 unobscuredBounds.origin.y += topContentInset;
4705 unobscuredBounds.size.height -= topContentInset;
4706 windowCaptureRect = [m_view convertRect:unobscuredBounds toView:nil];
4707 }
4708
4709 NSRect windowCaptureScreenRect = [window convertRectToScreen:windowCaptureRect];
4710 CGRect windowScreenRect;
4711 CGSGetScreenRectForWindow(CGSMainConnectionID(), (CGSWindowID)[window windowNumber], &windowScreenRect);
4712
4713 NSRect croppedImageRect = windowCaptureRect;
4714 croppedImageRect.origin.y = windowScreenRect.size.height - windowCaptureScreenRect.size.height - NSMinY(windowCaptureRect);
4715
4716 auto croppedSnapshotImage = adoptCF(CGImageCreateWithImageInRect(windowSnapshotImage.get(), NSRectToCGRect([window convertRectToBacking:croppedImageRect])));
4717
4718 auto surface = WebCore::IOSurface::createFromImage(croppedSnapshotImage.get());
4719 if (!surface)
4720 return nullptr;
4721
4722 auto snapshot = ViewSnapshot::create(WTFMove(surface));
4723 snapshot->setVolatile(true);
4724
4725 return WTFMove(snapshot);
4726}

4982static Vector<WebCore::CompositionUnderline> extractUnderlines(NSAttributedString *string)
4983{
4984 Vector<WebCore::CompositionUnderline> result;
4985 int length = string.string.length;
4986
4987 for (int i = 0; i < length;) {
4988 NSRange range;
4989 NSDictionary *attrs = [string attributesAtIndex:i longestEffectiveRange:&range inRange:NSMakeRange(i, length - i)];
4990
4991 if (NSNumber *style = [attrs objectForKey:NSUnderlineStyleAttributeName]) {
4992 WebCore::Color color = WebCore::Color::black;
4993 WebCore::CompositionUnderlineColor compositionUnderlineColor = WebCore::CompositionUnderlineColor::TextColor;
4994 if (NSColor *colorAttr = [attrs objectForKey:NSUnderlineColorAttributeName]) {
4995 color = WebCore::colorFromNSColor(colorAttr);
4996 compositionUnderlineColor = WebCore::CompositionUnderlineColor::GivenColor;
4997 }
4998 result.append(WebCore::CompositionUnderline(range.location, NSMaxRange(range), compositionUnderlineColor, color, style.intValue > 1));
4999 }
5000
5001 i = range.location + range.length;
5002 }
5003
5004 return result;
5005}

5008{
5009 unsigned short keyCode = [event keyCode];
5010 return !keyCode || keyCode == 10 || keyCode == 63;
5011}
5012
5013Vector<WebCore::KeypressCommand> WebViewImpl::collectKeyboardLayoutCommandsForEvent(NSEvent *event)
5014{
5015 Vector<WebCore::KeypressCommand> commands;
5016
5017 if ([event type] != NSEventTypeKeyDown)
5018 return commands;
5019
5020 ASSERT(!m_collectedKeypressCommands);
5021 m_collectedKeypressCommands = &commands;
5022
5023 if (NSTextInputContext *context = inputContext())
5024 [context handleEventByKeyboardLayout:event];
5025 else
5026 [m_view interpretKeyEvents:@[event]];
5027
5028 m_collectedKeypressCommands = nullptr;
5029
5030 return commands;
5031}
5032
5033void WebViewImpl::interpretKeyEvent(NSEvent *event, void(^completionHandler)(BOOL handled, const Vector<WebCore::KeypressCommand>& commands))
5034{
5035 // For regular Web content, input methods run before passing a keydown to DOM, but plug-ins get an opportunity to handle the event first.
5036 // There is no need to collect commands, as the plug-in cannot execute them.
5037 if (pluginComplexTextInputIdentifier()) {
5038 completionHandler(NO, { });
5039 return;
5040 }
5041
5042 if (!inputContext()) {
5043 auto commands = collectKeyboardLayoutCommandsForEvent(event);
5044 completionHandler(NO, commands);
5045 return;
5046 }
5047
5048 LOG(TextInput, "-> handleEventByInputMethod:%p %@", event, event);
5049 [inputContext() handleEventByInputMethod:event completionHandler:[weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this), capturedEvent = retainPtr(event), capturedBlock = makeBlockPtr(completionHandler)](BOOL handled) {
5050 if (!weakThis) {
5051 capturedBlock(NO, { });
5052 return;
5053 }
5054
5055 LOG(TextInput, "... handleEventByInputMethod%s handled", handled ? "" : " not");
5056 if (handled) {
5057 capturedBlock(YES, { });
5058 return;
5059 }
5060
5061 auto commands = weakThis->collectKeyboardLayoutCommandsForEvent(capturedEvent.get());
5062 capturedBlock(NO, commands);
5063 }];
5064}

5066void WebViewImpl::doCommandBySelector(SEL selector)
5067{
5068 LOG(TextInput, "doCommandBySelector:\"%s\"", sel_getName(selector));
5069
5070 if (auto* keypressCommands = m_collectedKeypressCommands) {
5071 WebCore::KeypressCommand command(NSStringFromSelector(selector));
5072 keypressCommands->append(command);
5073 LOG(TextInput, "...stored");
5074 m_page->registerKeypressCommandName(command.commandName);
5075 } else {
5076 // FIXME: Send the command to Editor synchronously and only send it along the
5077 // responder chain if it's a selector that does not correspond to an editing command.
5078 [m_view _web_superDoCommandBySelector:selector];
5079 }

5082void WebViewImpl::insertText(id string)
5083{
5084 // Unlike an NSTextInputClient variant with replacementRange, this NSResponder method is called when there is no input context,
5085 // so text input processing isn't performed. We are not going to actually insert any text in that case, but saving an insertText
5086 // command ensures that a keypress event is dispatched as appropriate.
5087 insertText(string, NSMakeRange(NSNotFound, 0));
5088}
5089
5090void WebViewImpl::insertText(id string, NSRange replacementRange)
5091{
5092 BOOL isAttributedString = [string isKindOfClass:[NSAttributedString class]];
5093 ASSERT(isAttributedString || [string isKindOfClass:[NSString class]]);
5094
5095 if (replacementRange.location != NSNotFound)
5096 LOG(TextInput, "insertText:\"%@\" replacementRange:(%u, %u)", isAttributedString ? [string string] : string, replacementRange.location, replacementRange.length);
5097 else
5098 LOG(TextInput, "insertText:\"%@\"", isAttributedString ? [string string] : string);
5099
5100 NSString *text;
5101 Vector<WebCore::TextAlternativeWithRange> dictationAlternatives;
5102
5103 bool registerUndoGroup = false;
5104 if (isAttributedString) {
5105 WebCore::collectDictationTextAlternatives(string, dictationAlternatives);
5106 registerUndoGroup = WebCore::shouldRegisterInsertionUndoGroup(string);
5107 // FIXME: We ignore most attributes from the string, so for example inserting from Character Palette loses font and glyph variation data.
5108 text = [string string];
5109 } else
5110 text = string;
5111
5112 m_isTextInsertionReplacingSoftSpace = false;
5113 if (m_softSpaceRange.location != NSNotFound && (replacementRange.location == NSMaxRange(m_softSpaceRange) || replacementRange.location == NSNotFound) && replacementRange.length == 0 && [[NSSpellChecker sharedSpellChecker] deletesAutospaceBeforeString:text language:nil]) {
5114 replacementRange = m_softSpaceRange;
5115 m_isTextInsertionReplacingSoftSpace = true;
5116 }
5117 m_softSpaceRange = NSMakeRange(NSNotFound, 0);
5118
5119 // insertText can be called for several reasons:
5120 // - If it's from normal key event processing (including key bindings), we save the action to perform it later.
5121 // - If it's from an input method, then we should insert the text now.
5122 // - If it's sent outside of keyboard event processing (e.g. from Character Viewer, or when confirming an inline input area with a mouse),
5123 // then we also execute it immediately, as there will be no other chance.
5124 Vector<WebCore::KeypressCommand>* keypressCommands = m_collectedKeypressCommands;
5125 if (keypressCommands && !m_isTextInsertionReplacingSoftSpace) {
5126 ASSERT(replacementRange.location == NSNotFound);
5127 WebCore::KeypressCommand command("insertText:", text);
5128 keypressCommands->append(command);
5129 LOG(TextInput, "...stored");
5130 m_page->registerKeypressCommandName(command.commandName);
5131 return;
5132 }
5133
5134 String eventText = text;
5135 eventText.replace(NSBackTabCharacter, NSTabCharacter); // same thing is done in KeyEventMac.mm in WebCore
5136 if (!dictationAlternatives.isEmpty()) {
5137 InsertTextOptions options;
5138 options.registerUndoGroup = registerUndoGroup;
5139 m_page->insertDictatedTextAsync(eventText, replacementRange, dictationAlternatives, WTFMove(options));
5140 } else {
5141 InsertTextOptions options;
5142 options.registerUndoGroup = registerUndoGroup;
5143 options.editingRangeIsRelativeTo = m_isTextInsertionReplacingSoftSpace ? EditingRangeIsRelativeTo::Paragraph : EditingRangeIsRelativeTo::EditableRoot;
5144 options.suppressSelectionUpdate = m_isTextInsertionReplacingSoftSpace;
5145
5146 m_page->insertTextAsync(eventText, replacementRange, WTFMove(options));
5147 }
5148}

5252{
5253 if (pluginComplexTextInputIdentifier()) {
5254 ASSERT(!m_collectedKeypressCommands); // Should not get here from -_interpretKeyEvent:completionHandler:, we only use WKTextInputWindowController after giving the plug-in a chance to handle keydown natively.
