5272void WebViewImpl::setMarkedText(id string, NSRange selectedRange, NSRange replacementRange)
5273{
5274 BOOL isAttributedString = [string isKindOfClass:[NSAttributedString class]];
5275 ASSERT(isAttributedString || [string isKindOfClass:[NSString class]]);
5276
5277 LOG(TextInput, "setMarkedText:\"%@\" selectedRange:(%u, %u) replacementRange:(%u, %u)", isAttributedString ? [string string] : string, selectedRange.location, selectedRange.length, replacementRange.location, replacementRange.length);
5278
5279 Vector<WebCore::CompositionUnderline> underlines;
5280 NSString *text;
5281
5282 if (isAttributedString) {
5283 // FIXME: We ignore most attributes from the string, so an input method cannot specify e.g. a font or a glyph variation.
5284 text = [string string];
5285 underlines = extractUnderlines(string);
5286 } else {
5287 text = string;
5288 underlines.append(WebCore::CompositionUnderline(0, [text length], WebCore::CompositionUnderlineColor::TextColor, WebCore::Color::black, false));
5289 }
5290
5291 if (inSecureInputState()) {
5292 // In password fields, we only allow ASCII dead keys, and don't allow inline input, matching NSSecureTextInputField.
5293 // Allowing ASCII dead keys is necessary to enable full Roman input when using a Vietnamese keyboard.
5294 ASSERT(!m_page->editorState().hasComposition);
5295 notifyInputContextAboutDiscardedComposition();
5296 // FIXME: We should store the command to handle it after DOM event processing, as it's regular keyboard input now, not a composition.
5297 if ([text length] == 1 && isASCII([text characterAtIndex:0]))
5298 m_page->insertTextAsync(text, replacementRange, { });
5299 else
5300 NSBeep();
5301 return;
5302 }
5303
5304 m_page->setCompositionAsync(text, underlines, { }, selectedRange, replacementRange);
5305}

5344
5345bool WebViewImpl::performKeyEquivalent(NSEvent *event)
5346{
5347 if (ignoresNonWheelEvents())
5348 return NO;
5349
5350 // There's a chance that responding to this event will run a nested event loop, and
5351 // fetching a new event might release the old one. Retaining and then autoreleasing
5352 // the current event prevents that from causing a problem inside WebKit or AppKit code.
5353 retainPtr(event).autorelease();
5354
5355 // We get Esc key here after processing either Esc or Cmd+period. The former starts as a keyDown, and the latter starts as a key equivalent,
5356 // but both get transformed to a cancelOperation: command, executing which passes an Esc key event to -performKeyEquivalent:.
5357 // Don't interpret this event again, avoiding re-entrancy and infinite loops.
5358 if ([[event charactersIgnoringModifiers] isEqualToString:@"\e"] && !([event modifierFlags] & NSEventModifierFlagDeviceIndependentFlagsMask))
5359 return [m_view _web_superPerformKeyEquivalent:event];
5360
5361 if (m_keyDownEventBeingResent) {
5362 // WebCore has already seen the event, no need for custom processing.
5363 // Note that we can get multiple events for each event being re-sent. For example, for Cmd+'=' AppKit
5364 // first performs the original key equivalent, and if that isn't handled, it dispatches a synthetic Cmd+'+'.
5365 return [m_view _web_superPerformKeyEquivalent:event];
5366 }
5367
5368 disableComplexTextInputIfNecessary();
5369
5370 // Pass key combos through WebCore if there is a key binding available for
5371 // this event. This lets webpages have a crack at intercepting key-modified keypresses.
5372 // FIXME: Why is the firstResponder check needed?
5373 if (m_view.getAutoreleased() == [m_view window].firstResponder) {
5374 interpretKeyEvent(event, [weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this), capturedEvent = retainPtr(event)](BOOL handledByInputMethod, const Vector<WebCore::KeypressCommand>& commands) {
5375 if (weakThis)
5376 weakThis->m_page->handleKeyboardEvent(NativeWebKeyboardEvent(capturedEvent.get(), handledByInputMethod, false, commands));
5377 });
5378 return YES;
5379 }
5380
5381 return [m_view _web_superPerformKeyEquivalent:event];
5382}

5385{
5386 if (ignoresNonWheelEvents())
5387 return;
5388
5389 LOG(TextInput, "keyUp:%p %@", event, event);
5390
5391 m_isTextInsertionReplacingSoftSpace = false;
5392 interpretKeyEvent(event, [weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this), capturedEvent = retainPtr(event)](BOOL handledByInputMethod, const Vector<WebCore::KeypressCommand>& commands) {
5393 ASSERT(!handledByInputMethod || commands.isEmpty());
5394 if (weakThis)

5396 });

5399void WebViewImpl::keyDown(NSEvent *event)
5400{
5401 if (ignoresNonWheelEvents())
5402 return;
5403
5404 LOG(TextInput, "keyDown:%p %@%s", event, event, (event == m_keyDownEventBeingResent) ? " (re-sent)" : "");
5405
5406 if (tryHandlePluginComplexTextInputKeyDown(event)) {
5407 LOG(TextInput, "...handled by plug-in");
5408 return;
5409 }
5410
5411 // We could be receiving a key down from AppKit if we have re-sent an event
5412 // that maps to an action that is currently unavailable (for example a copy when
5413 // there is no range selection).
5414 // If this is the case we should ignore the key down.
5415 if (m_keyDownEventBeingResent == event) {
5416 [m_view _web_superKeyDown:event];
5417 return;
5418 }
5419
5420 m_isTextInsertionReplacingSoftSpace = false;
5421 interpretKeyEvent(event, [weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this), capturedEvent = retainPtr(event)](BOOL handledByInputMethod, const Vector<WebCore::KeypressCommand>& commands) {
5422 ASSERT(!handledByInputMethod || commands.isEmpty());
5423 if (weakThis)
5424 weakThis->m_page->handleKeyboardEvent(NativeWebKeyboardEvent(capturedEvent.get(), handledByInputMethod, weakThis->m_isTextInsertionReplacingSoftSpace, commands));
5425 });
5426}

5438

5442 });

5472void WebViewImpl::nativeMouseEventHandler(NSEvent *event)
5473{
5474 if (m_ignoresNonWheelEvents)
5475 return;
5476
5477 if (NSTextInputContext *context = [m_view inputContext]) {
5478 auto weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this);

5480 [context handleEvent:event completionHandler:[weakThis, retainedEvent] (BOOL handled) {

5487 weakThis->m_page->handleMouseEvent(webEvent);
5488 }
5489 }];
5490 return;
5491 }

5493 m_page->handleMouseEvent(webEvent);
5494}

5600 if (m_page->rubberBandsAtRight())

5602 if (m_page->rubberBandsAtTop())

5604 if (m_page->rubberBandsAtBottom())

5606 return state;

5741bool WebViewImpl::canHandleContextMenuTranslation() const
5742{
5743 return TranslationUIServicesLibrary() && [getLTUITranslationViewControllerClass() isAvailable];
5744}
5745
5746void WebViewImpl::handleContextMenuTranslation(const WebCore::TranslationContextMenuInfo& info)
5747{
5748 if (!canHandleContextMenuTranslation()) {
5749 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
5750 return;
5751 }
5752
5753 auto view = m_view.get();
5754 auto translationViewController = adoptNS([allocLTUITranslationViewControllerInstance() init]);
5755 [translationViewController setText:adoptNS([[NSAttributedString alloc] initWithString:info.text]).get()];
5756 if (info.mode == WebCore::TranslationContextMenuMode::Editable && [translationViewController respondsToSelector:@selector(setReplacementHandler:)]) {
5757 [translationViewController setIsSourceEditable:YES];
5758 [translationViewController setReplacementHandler:[this, weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this)](NSAttributedString *string) {
5759 if (weakThis)
5760 insertText(string.string);
5761 }];
5762 }
5763
5764 if (NSEqualSizes([translationViewController preferredContentSize], NSZeroSize))
5765 [translationViewController setPreferredContentSize:NSMakeSize(400, 400)];
5766
5767 auto popover = adoptNS([[NSPopover alloc] init]);
5768 [popover setBehavior:NSPopoverBehaviorTransient];
5769 [popover setAppearance:[view effectiveAppearance]];
5770 [popover setAnimates:YES];
5771 [popover setContentViewController:translationViewController.get()];
5772 [popover setContentSize:[translationViewController preferredContentSize]];
5773
5774 NSRectEdge preferredEdge;
5775 auto aim = info.locationInRootView.x();
5776 auto highlight = info.selectionBoundsInRootView.center().x();
5777 if (aim == highlight)
5778 preferredEdge = [view userInterfaceLayoutDirection] == NSUserInterfaceLayoutDirectionRightToLeft ? NSRectEdgeMinX : NSRectEdgeMaxX;
5779 else
5780 preferredEdge = aim > highlight ? NSRectEdgeMaxX : NSRectEdgeMinX;
5781
5782 [popover showRelativeToRect:info.selectionBoundsInRootView ofView:view.get() preferredEdge:preferredEdge];
5783}
